peed 1.5<b>."},{"content":"Add reserved cheddar and cauliflower and half of the reserved Parmesan, then stir through with aid of spatula. Cook <b>9 min\/90°C\/\/speed 1.5<b> or until rice is tender. Allow to cool slightly, then serve topped with remaining Parmesan."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can replace liquid vegetable stock with Vegetable stock paste and water in this recipe. Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe. In step 8 replace liquid stock with 2 teaspoons Vegetable stock paste and 200 g water.","Adding hidden cauliflower to risotto is a great way to give your child an extra serve of vegetable and a nutrient boost. You might also like to serve some 'visible' steamed cauliflower on the side so that your child becomes accustomed to seeing and tasting cauliflower on its own too."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","4 portions"]}